Exactly-Once Semantics Guarantor

Create exactly-once semantics where Express implements idempotent endpoints, MongoDB stores processed request IDs. Node.js deduplicates in-flight requests preventing double-processing, shell scripts cleans up old dedup entries, Git tracks exactly-once semantics changes, Unix atomic operations ensure transactional safety, and implement idempotency token validation with TTL preventing ID collision.

